A worker came to repair the kitchen floor, and I pretended to be working from home, but in reality, I was editing "Addicted."
If only this damn file would open. (OneDrive is truly shit.)
*Hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the noise was super loud. Awesome.
Turn the air purifier up to the highest setting—it feels a little too aggressive, but I did smell the wood shavings, so it's understandable, especially since he's against wearing masks. And I do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can't sleep until he leaves.
Good news is, Chapter Four is finally edited!
Chapter Five is really long and super anxiety-inducing. Yay! It's so exciting.
Searching and replacing... ➡️ ellipsis, this chapter has a total of 54 😅
But I still stand by this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally agitated.
The floor repairman is vacuuming, hoping this means he's nearly done.
He went out (it sounded like) cutting something. I sneakily checked the progress. There's still a lot of work to do :(
Chapter Five has seven pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in quite a good state, mainly requiring formatting adjustments and some minor changes to active voice and conciseness. But I really need to take a break, have a cup of tea, while that guy is still busy in my kitchen.
He's started vacuuming again. Hopefully, this is a good omen.
The worker who was fixing the kitchen floor is gone!
He told me he quoted for the repair of the entire floor, but the landlord is so cheap, only willing to pay for the repair of the rotten part near the door. Feels much better.
I'm having tea in the garden, while the air purifier is working hard in the kitchen, purifying the air in the room!
